  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "m0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "# bangla-text-toolkit — End-to-End Demo\n\nA walkthrough of every component in the library, from raw Bangla Unicode text to fixed-length token embeddings.\n\nAll processing is **zero-dependency pure Python** — no NumPy, no NLTK, no spaCy.\n\n---\n**Library:** `bangla-text-toolkit`  \n**Author:** Umme Abira Azmary · [github.com/Mouly22](https://github.com/Mouly22)  \n**Repo:** [github.com/Mouly22/bangla-text-toolkit](https://github.com/Mouly22/bangla-text-toolkit)"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "m0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 0. Install"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "# pip install bangla-text-toolkit\n# Or from source:\n# git clone https://github.com/Mouly22/bangla-text-toolkit.git && pip install -e \".[dev]\"\n",
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "m0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 1. Text Normalisation\n\n`BanglaTextNormalizer` handles Unicode NFC, zero-width characters, whitespace collapsing, punctuation and digit normalisation."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "from bangla_text_toolkit import BanglaTextNormalizer\n\nnorm = BanglaTextNormalizer(digit_mode=\"ascii\")\n\nraw = \"আমি  বাংলায়\\u200b গান\\u200c গাই!  ০১২৩\"\nclean = norm.normalize(raw)\nprint(repr(clean))",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "output_type": "stream",
     "name": "stdout",
     "text": "'আমি বাংলায় গান গাই! 0123'\\n"
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "m0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 2. Text Cleaning\n\n`BanglaTextCleaner` strips noise: URLs, HTML tags, emails, emojis, mentions, hashtags."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "from bangla_text_toolkit.cleaner import BanglaTextCleaner\n\ncleaner = BanglaTextCleaner(remove_urls=True, remove_emojis=True, remove_html=True)\n\nnoisy = \"দেখো https://example.com <b>বাংলা</b> টেক্সট 😊 @user #NLP\"\nprint(cleaner.clean(noisy))",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "output_type": "stream",
     "name": "stdout",
     "text": "দেখো  বাংলা টেক্সট   \\n"
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "m0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 3. Pipeline composition\n\nChain any callables with `Pipeline`. Steps run left-to-right; each step receives the previous step's output."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "from bangla_text_toolkit.pipeline import Pipeline\n\npipe = Pipeline()\npipe.add_step(BanglaTextCleaner(remove_urls=True).clean)\npipe.add_step(BanglaTextNormalizer().normalize)\n\nresult = pipe.run(\"আমি  https://example.com বাংলায় ০১২ গান গাই!\")\nprint(result)",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "output_type": "stream",
     "name": "stdout",
     "text": "আমি  বাংলায় ০১২ গান গাই!\\n"
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "m0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 4. Tokenisation\n\n`BanglaTokenizer` uses Bangla-aware regex that correctly handles combining vowel signs (matras)."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "from bangla_text_toolkit.tokenizer import BanglaTokenizer\n\ntok = BanglaTokenizer()\n\ntext = \"আমি বাংলায় গান গাই। সে বাংলায় কথা বলে।\"\n\nwords = tok.tokenize(text)\nprint(\"Tokens :\", words)\n\nsentences = tok.sent_tokenize(text)\nprint(\"Sentences:\", sentences)",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "output_type": "stream",
     "name": "stdout",
     "text": "Tokens : ['আমি', 'বাংলায়', 'গান', 'গাই', 'সে', 'বাংলায়', 'কথা', 'বলে']\\nSentences: ['আমি বাংলায় গান গাই।', 'সে বাংলায় কথা বলে।']\\n"
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "m0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 5. Stopwords\n\nBuilt-in set of 100+ Bangla function words. `remove_stopwords` filters them from a token list."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "from bangla_text_toolkit.tokenizer import remove_stopwords\nfrom bangla_text_toolkit.stopwords import get_stopwords\n\ntokens = tok.tokenize(\"আমি বাংলায় গান গাই\")\nprint(\"Before:\", tokens)\n\ncontent_words = remove_stopwords(tokens)\nprint(\"After :\", content_words)\n\nsw = get_stopwords()\nprint(f\"Stopword set size: {len(sw)}\")",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "output_type": "stream",
     "name": "stdout",
     "text": "Before: ['আমি', 'বাংলায়', 'গান', 'গাই']\\nAfter : ['গান', 'গাই']\\nStopword set size: 60\\n"
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "m0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 6. Romanisation\n\n`BanglaRomanizer` converts Bangla Unicode to a Roman transliteration using rule-based character mapping."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "from bangla_text_toolkit.romanization import BanglaRomanizer\n\nrom = BanglaRomanizer()\n\nwords = [\"বাংলা\", \"আমি\", \"গান\", \"ভালোবাসি\"]\nfor w in words:\n    print(f\"  {w:12s} → {rom.romanize(w)}\")",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "output_type": "stream",
     "name": "stdout",
     "text": "  বাংলা       → bangla\\n  আমি          → ami\\n  গান          → gan\\n  ভালোবাসি    → bhalobasi\\n"
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "m0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 7. Stemming\n\n`BanglaStemmer` strips common Bangla suffixes: plural markers, case suffixes, tense suffixes."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "c0",
   "metadata": {},
